To the right of the design, the text "VATSIM Germany" is written, with "VATSIM" in blue and "Germany" in gray. Below the text, there are three small circles in the colors of the German flag: black, red, and yellow. The logo also includes a small gray symbol resembling an aircraft or navigation tool.

The image consists of a logo divided into two sections. The left section features the NATO emblem, which is a white compass rose on a blue background. The right section contains the text "VIRTUAL NATO" in white letters on a dark blue background. The design suggests a digital or online representation of NATO.

metadata.abstract: The document titled 'Military' pertains to the Letter of Agreement between VATSIM Germany and Virtual NATO (VNATO). The agreement aims to ensure smooth and efficient communication and procedures for military flights and activities. The document includes details on the roles and responsibilities of both parties, as well as the operational guidelines to be followed. This agreement is crucial for maintaining order and safety in the virtual airspace during military operations.
